# windows/.links — Windows tier deploy manifest.
#
# One line per managed app:   <app><TAB><destination>
#   - <app> is a dir or file under windows/ (e.g. `starship.toml`, `gh`).
#   - <destination> is an absolute path whose LEADING env reference is
#     expanded at deploy time. Recognized (prefix only, no other expansion,
#     no eval, no globbing): $HOME/.config, $HOME, $APPDATA, $LOCALAPPDATA,
#     $USERPROFILE.
#   - Fields are separated by a single TAB, so destinations may contain spaces.
#   - Anything after a SECOND TAB is an inline comment and is ignored, so a
#     line may carry a trailing note: <app><TAB><destination><TAB># note
#   - Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored; surrounding
#     whitespace is trimmed.
#
# deploy_manifest (lib/link.sh) links each destination -> windows/<app> using
# backup-then-link. The manifest itself and windows/setup/ are never deployed.
#
# No app configs ship in this stub yet. Add lines as Windows configs land —
# uncomment/adjust the examples below (they already use a real TAB separator):
#
# starship.toml	$HOME/.config/starship.toml	# XDG-aware CLI
# gh	$HOME/.config/gh	# XDG-aware CLI
# code	$APPDATA/Code/User	# GUI app (VS Code)
